    • Method Detail

      • setAddress

        public boolean setAddress(long address)
                   throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        This method sets a new value for the address. If the address was successfully set, this method returns true. If the address couldn't be set, because it is out of the allowed limits, this method returns false. If the given address is negativ, an IllegalArgumentException is thrown. A given address must not be negative.
        Parameters:
        address - the new address as positive integer
        Returns:
        true if the address was set correctly
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the given address was negative

      • getBytes

        public byte[] getBytes()
        Description copied from interface: Parameter
        This method returns the data of this Parameter as byte array. This array should be sorted correctly (least significant byte first). This method is likely called to get the data that should be written to the device.
        Returns:
        the data of this Parameter, ready to be written to the device

      • isValid

        public boolean isValid()
        Description copied from interface: Parameter
        This method should return whether the data for this parameter is valid or not. If there are no restrictions to be checked, it should return true.
        Returns:
        true if the data is valid and could possibly be send to the device without forcing an error
